name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: mapreduce.reduce.shuffle.fetch.retry.interval-ms
description:
Time of interval that fetcher retry to fetch again when some
  non-fatal failure happens because of some events like NM restart.

name: hadoop.security.uid.cache.secs
description:
This is the config controlling the validity of the entries in the cache
        containing the userId to userName and groupId to groupName used by
        NativeIO getFstat().

name: dfs.datanode.directoryscan.interval
description:
Interval in seconds for Datanode to scan data directories and
  reconcile the difference between blocks in memory and on the disk.
  Support multiple time unit suffix(case insensitive), as described
  in dfs.heartbeat.interval.If no time unit is specified then seconds
  is assumed.

name: dfs.namenode.fs-limits.max-directory-items
description:
Defines the maximum number of items that a directory may
      contain. Cannot set the property to a value less than 1 or more than
      6400000.

name: hadoop.security.kms.client.authentication.retry-count
description: Number of time to retry connecting to KMS on authentication failure

name: mapreduce.shuffle.pathcache.concurrency-level
description:
Uses the concurrency level to create a fixed number of hashtable
    segments, each governed by its own write lock.
